<Layout title="Pharmacist Mortgage · Retail Chain W-2, Hospital Clinical Specialty, Independent Community Pharmacy S-Corp &amp; PharmD IDR-Aware Specialist" description="Pharmacist mortgage for new-grad PharmDs starting first retail chain (CVS, Walgreens, Walmart, Costco) or hospital pharmacy position with $150K-$250K PharmD student loans on IDR, established staff and pharmacy manager pharmacists with relief/PRN W-2 supplementation across multiple chains, hospital clinical specialty pharmacists with BPS board certifications (BCPS Pharmacotherapy, BCOP Oncology, BCIDP Infectious Disease, BCCP Cardiology, BCPP Psychiatry, BCACP Ambulatory Care), independent community pharmacy owners with S-corp K-1 distributions, and specialty and compounding pharmacy owners operating under USP 797/800 standards for sterile and hazardous drug compounding including GLP-1 semaglutide and tirzepatide compounding during FDA shortage periods, bioidentical hormone replacement therapy compounding, sterile IV compounding for infusion practices, and veterinary compounding. Critical contrast: pharmacists are NOT typically eligible for Physician/Doctor Loan products at most specialty lenders (key difference from physicians, NPs, and PAs). Optimal mortgage path is Conventional Conforming or Jumbo with Fannie Mae B3-6-05 IDR-aware DTI treatment for PharmD student loan burden (actual servicer payment at $400-$1,200/month vs $1,500-$2,500 under 1 percent rule). Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01 chain or hospital W-2 with BPS specialty premium variable income treatment, B3-3.3-02 consulting 1099-NEC self-employment aggregation (pharmacy benefit consulting, formulary management, expert witness), and B3-3.4-02 pharmacy S-corp W-2 reasonable compensation plus K-1 distributions with Form 1084 cash-flow addbacks for compounding equipment and robotic dispensing system Section 179 expensing. APhA, ASHP, NABP, ACPE, BPS, and USP industry context. PSLF eligibility for nonprofit hospital, VA Medical Center, and Indian Health Service pharmacists. SBA 7(a) coordination for pharmacy acquisition financing." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/medical-professionals/pharmacist/">
  <div class="pharmacist-scope" set:html={pharmacistBody} />
</Layout>

<style is:global>
